    :markdown
      I am born and raised in Sweden (Stockholm) where I finished my studies in [Interactions Design](/experience) and thus started my web-journey.

      In 2008 I joined [Redbet](/showcase/redbet), a (then) small i-gaming sprout in Stockholm. Working with Ramaze a lot, I developed a great fondness for Ruby and the MVC pattern. After two years I transferred to Malta in 2010 to start up and lead the front-end team there.

    %p
      In late 2013 I decided to leave Malta and the i-gaming industry, to work with

      %a{ :href => 'http://x-team.com', :title => 'X-Team', :target => '_blank' }
        X-Team

      and learn what it means to work remotely.

      X-Team is an incredible bunch of people that does a great job at putting together people from all over the world with all kinds of cultures and useful skills to build cool and widely recognized applications.

    %p
      By 2014 my interest moved towards Javascript more and more. At Aviso, an Irish company working with payment technology, I really got to delve deep into the rich client-side application development, with AngularJS, ClojureScript, ReactJS and Reagent.

    %p
      With Aviso moving aways from AngularJS, I got introduced to MyTalengi and Keeper Solutions where I would really get to work with one of my favorites - BackboneJS.

